WhatsNew_CopyTaskWithDayCards_Content: You can now copy tasks with day cards, in order to repeat more detailed workflow patterns.
WhatsNew_CopyTaskWithDayCards_Title: Copy tasks with day cards by default
WhatsNew_DifferentWorkareaMultipleTasksS: Users can now multi-select tasks from across different working areas, in order to delete or change the status of even more tasks at once.
Select multiple tasks from different working areas
WhatsNew_MoveCopyTaskWithCommandBar_Cont: Tablet users in particular now can visibly chose between moving or copying tasks. Start multi-selecting tasks in the calendar, and then the options to move or copy them are visible in the bottom command bar.

WhatsNew_MultipleTasksStatusChange_Conte: Users now can delete or change the status of multiple tasks at once. Click the three dots icon in the bottom command bar after selecting multiple tasks, and save time performing updates.

WhatsNew_NonWorkingDays_Content: The superintendent can now define non-working days such as weekends and holidays for the project team. Just open Settings and go to "Working days".

WhatsNew_TaskUpdateFlags_Content: Every user can activate task update flags to immediately see which task has news. Click the three dots icon in the top right corner of the calendar and select “Show task update flags”.
